@startuml
title Automation Framework - Module: imaging

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

package "imaging" {
  component "opencv/base.py\nOpenCVAdapterBase" as AdapterBase
  component "_path_image_cache()" as Cache
  component "require_cv2() /\nrequire_numpy() /\nrequire_pillow()" as DependencyGuards
  component "to_ndarray() /\nclip_region() /\npreprocess()" as Operations
}

package "Primary Consumers" {
  component "vision.detectors" as Detectors
  component "vision.ocr" as OCR
  component "vision.opencv\nmatchers / readers /\ncomparators" as OpenCVVision
}

AdapterBase --> Cache
AdapterBase --> DependencyGuards
AdapterBase --> Operations
Detectors --> AdapterBase
OCR --> AdapterBase
OpenCVVision --> AdapterBase

note bottom of AdapterBase
  The imaging module is a shared technical utility layer.
  It centralizes OpenCV dependency checks, image coercion,
  path caching, cropping, and preprocessing.
end note

@enduml
